{
  "texts": [
    "We use contrastive learning (triplet margin loss) to minimize the impact of known confounders v on z.",
    "For example, this ensures that all the cancer samples from different sources are projected in proximity of each other (see Triplet Margin Loss section).",
    "(a) Minimize the distance between samples that have the same label (e.g.",
    "all cancer samples or all control samples) but are from a different confounder group (e.g.",
    "source, supplier, etc.)"
  ]
}